rComments: Took MANAGEMENT OF INNOVATION with him in English. He is bilingual so you can answer your test or do your briefing notes in French as well. He is focused on the success of his students and gives you the tools to excel. His accent took some adjusting but otherwise great prof.
He wants people to pass, but still, students need to work hard

Well he is a caring prof and was fairly generous and motivating in his grading of the assignments I've received thus far. That said, his grading criteria and requirements are unclear and he really needs to be more clear & concise in his lectures; his speech is also at times undiscernible and it becomes really hard to stay focused in class.

Chahreddine is a great prof. His classes are mainly discussions with students, and if you participate in them, you're pretty much guaranteed an A in the class. The discussions are high level summaries of the content that are learned in class, and are great to benchmark ones understanding of the course content. TAKE THIS PROF FOR ALL CLASSES!
